Missing `IPFamilyPolicy` and `IPFamilies` normalization — causes spurious Service updates on every reconcile.

`ServiceSpecDefaults` normalizes `Type`, `SessionAffinity`, `InternalTrafficPolicy`, and `Port.Protocol`, but omits two fields the Kubernetes API server populates on every newly created Service:

| Field | API-server default |
|---|---|
| `IPFamilyPolicy` | `"SingleStack"` |
| `IPFamilies` | `["IPv4"]` (IPv4 cluster) or `["IPv6"]` (IPv6 cluster) |

After first creation, `existingSpec.IPFamilyPolicy == &"SingleStack"` while `newSpec.IPFamilyPolicy == nil`. Because `reflect.DeepEqual(nil, &"SingleStack")` is `false`, `apiequality.Semantic.DeepEqual(existingSpec, newSpec)` returns `false` on every subsequent reconcile — triggering `c.Update` in `EnsureService` on every pass. The API server reapplies the default, and the loop repeats. This produces continuous unnecessary updates and watch events.

`IPFamilyPolicy` can be statically defaulted. `IPFamilies` is cluster-dependent, so it should instead be preserved from the existing spec in `EnsureService` (mirroring how `ClusterIP` is already handled):

```suggestion
func ServiceSpecDefaults(spec *corev1.ServiceSpec) {
	if spec.Type == "" {
		spec.Type = corev1.ServiceTypeClusterIP
	}
	if spec.SessionAffinity == "" {
		spec.SessionAffinity = corev1.ServiceAffinityNone
	}
	if spec.InternalTrafficPolicy == nil {
		cluster := corev1.ServiceInternalTrafficPolicyCluster
		spec.InternalTrafficPolicy = &cluster
	}
	if spec.IPFamilyPolicy == nil {
		singleStack := corev1.IPFamilyPolicySingleStack
		spec.IPFamilyPolicy = &singleStack
	}
	for i := range spec.Ports {
		if spec.Ports[i].Protocol == "" {
			spec.Ports[i].Protocol = corev1.ProtocolTCP
		}
	}
}
```

Also in `EnsureService` (around line 92-93), preserve `IPFamilies` from the existing spec:

```go
newSpec.ClusterIP = existing.Spec.ClusterIP
newSpec.ClusterIPs = existing.Spec.ClusterIPs
newSpec.IPFamilies = existing.Spec.IPFamilies   // preserve API-server-assigned IP families
```

